# Claude Code Web environment overrides
# Sources: base.env -> test.env -> claude-web.env (via setup-env.sh --mode=claude-web)
#
# This file overrides test.env defaults for Claude Code remote environments
# where Docker is unavailable and services run natively (PostgreSQL, Redis).
#
# Key differences from test.env:
#   - PGMQ messaging backend (no RabbitMQ service needed)
#   - PGMQ_DATABASE_URL set to main DB (single-database mode with PGMQ extension)
#   - Quieter log level for cleaner test output
#
# Usage:
#   cargo make setup-env-claude-web    # Creates .env from this overlay

# Messaging: PGMQ (simpler, shares PostgreSQL - no separate broker needed)
TASKER_MESSAGING_BACKEND=pgmq

# PGMQ database: same as main DB in single-database mode
# This must be explicitly set - the config default is empty and causes hangs
PGMQ_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://tasker:tasker@localhost:5432/tasker_rust_test

# Quieter logging for test runs (test.env defaults to info via base.env)
RUST_LOG=warn
LOG_LEVEL=warn
